What Constitutional Role does the ATF actually have?

Alcohol is a state regulated function (Reference: 21st Amendment and the 10th Amendment).

Tobacco is crop making it state concern. The distribution across state lines falls under the "Commerce Clause" (Article 1, Section 8, Clause 3). A law enforcement agency is needed for distribution of tobacco?

Firearms - From the 2nd Amendment "A well regulated Militia, being necessary to the security of a free STATE, the right of the people to keep and bear Arms, shall not be infringed." It does not say United States. The regulatory authority is State not Federal. 

The only real federal concern is the "Commerce Clause" portion of the distribution of products among the several states. The ATF has often gotten itself involved in point of sales issue between a local store and the customer. Those sales are NOT federal concerns Constitutionally speaking. They are state.
